[[ダウンロード: calling_test.go(Go)]] 
package calling

import "testing"

func pureFunc() error {
	return nil
}

func Benchmark_PureFunc(b *testing.B) {
	for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
		pureFunc()
	}
}

type someObj struct {
}

func (someObj) methodFunc() error {
	return nil
}

func Benchmark_ObjectMethod(b *testing.B) {
	o := someObj{}
	b.ResetTimer()
	for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
		o.methodFunc()
	}
}

func Benchmark_FuncVar(b *testing.B) {
	f := pureFunc
	b.ResetTimer()
	for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
		f()
	}
}

type methoder interface {
	methodFunc() error
}

func Benchmark_Interface(b *testing.B) {
	var m methoder = someObj{}
	b.ResetTimer()
	for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
		m.methodFunc()
	}
}

var m123 methoder = someObj{}

func Benchmark_FuncVar_Interface(b *testing.B) {
	var f func() error = m123.methodFunc
	b.ResetTimer()
	for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
		f()
	}
}

package main

import "testing"

func setup() []int {
	slice := make([]int, 1000)
	slice[999] = 1
	return slice
}

func BenchmarkInSlice(b *testing.B) {
	slice := setup()
	b.ResetTimer()
	for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
		for _, s := range slice {
			if s == 1 {
				return
			}
		}
	}
}

func BenchmarkInMap(b *testing.B) {
	slice := setup()
	b.ResetTimer()
	for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
		m := map[int]struct{}{}
		for _, s := range slice {
			m[s] = struct{}{}
		}

		if _, ok := m[1]; ok {
			return
		}
	}
}

package main

import (
	"math/rand"
	"testing"
)

func setupSlice(n int) []int {
	slice := make([]int, n)
	for i := 0; i < n; i++ {
		slice[i] = rand.Intn(n * 2)
	}
	return slice
}

func Benchmark_InSlice(b *testing.B) {
	slice := setupSlice(1000000)
	b.ResetTimer()
	count := 0
	for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
		for _, s := range slice {
			if s == i {
				count++
				break
			}
		}
	}
	//b.Logf("count=%d", count)
}

func setupSet(n int) map[int]struct{} {
	set := make(map[int]struct{}, n)
	for i := 0; i < n; i++ {
		set[rand.Intn(n*2)] = struct{}{}
	}
	return set
}

func Benchmark_InMap(b *testing.B) {
	set := setupSet(1000000)
	b.ResetTimer()
	count := 0
	for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {
		if _, ok := set[i]; ok {
			count++
		}
	}
	//b.Logf("count=%d", count)
}

clean:
	-@rm -f $(BINS)
